For the fiscal year 2020, Nvidia reported earnings of US$2.796 billion on revenue of US$10.918 billion, a slight decrease from the previous year. By January 2021, Nvidia's shares traded at over $531, with a market capitalization exceeding US$328.7 billion.

The second quarter of 2020 saw Nvidia report a significant 50% surge in sales to $3.87 billion compared to the same period in 2019, attributed to increased demand for technology amid the pandemic. CFO Colette Kress noted the company's focus on technologies supporting remote work. In May 2023, Nvidia's market valuation crossed $1 trillion during trading hours, reaching $1.2 trillion by November of the same year.

